testcase.name: test that it will confirm that a successful authentication and authorization can be determined by status code 200, LTPA TOKEN exists and no error
test that it will confirm that a successful authentication and authorization can be determined by status code 200, LTPA TOKEN exists and no error with new login response
test that it will confirm that a successful authentication and authorization with roles can be determined by status code 200, LTPA TOKEN exists and no error
test that it will confirm that a successful authentication but failed authorization will result in a login failure
test that it will confirm that a failed authentication and authorization can be determined by status code 403 and no LTPA Token
test that it will confirm that a failed EmployerID lookup will also be considered a failed login
test that it will confirm that a failed EmployerID lookup can get the error message from the response
test that it will confirm that a failed EmployerID lookup can get the right bundle code for the error message
test that it will confirm that a failed authentication and authorization which has a status code 403 and no LTPA Token will return default bundle code for error message
